1) What is inter-thread communication? How to implement by using wait(), notify(), and notifyAll() methods?
-->Inter-thread communication is the process where threads communicate with each other to coordinate execution.
Methods used:
  wait()
  notify()
  notifyAll()

These methods belong to the Object class.
wait():
  Makes thread wait until another thread notifies it.

notify()
  Wakes up one waiting thread.

notifyAll():
  Wakes up all waiting threads.



2) Why can these (wait(), notify(), and notifyAll()) methods be called only inside synchronized blocks?
-->Because the thread must own the object's monitor lock before calling these methods.
    Without synchronization:
        IllegalMonitorStateException occurs.



3) What is the difference between sleep() and wait()?
-->
| sleep()                          | wait()                              |
| -------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Belongs to Thread class          | Belongs to Object class             |
| Used for delay                   | Used for inter-thread communication |
| Does not release lock            | Releases lock                       |
| Automatically resumes after time | Resumes after notify()              |



4) What is a daemon thread? How do you create and identify a daemon thread?
-->A daemon thread is a background thread that provides services to user threads.
    Example:
    
    Garbage Collector
    Create daemon thread
    Thread t = new Thread();
    
    t.setDaemon(true);
    Identify daemon thread
    System.out.println(t.isDaemon());

